<h2 id="what-is-podium">📱 What Is Podium?</h2>

Podium is an all-in-one customer communication platform that consolidates text messaging, review management, webchat, and payments into a single dashboard. Originally built for auto dealerships, it has become the de facto standard for med spas, dental practices, and service businesses that live and die by local reputation.

The core value proposition is simple: meet patients where they already are (text messages) and make it frictionless for happy patients to leave reviews. In 2026, Podium has expanded into AI-powered lead nurturing, appointment scheduling integrations, and team performance analytics.

For med spas specifically, Podium solves the "we called and left a voicemail" problem. Nobody under 45 listens to voicemails anymore. When a lead fills out your contact form, Podium can auto-text them within seconds. That speed-to-lead advantage compounds — practices using Podium report 3x higher conversion rates on inbound leads compared to call-first workflows.

<h2 id="our-experience">🏢 Our Experience Managing Thousands of Locations</h2>

Our team has deployed Podium across med spa groups ranging from 3 to 47 locations. We've seen what works, what breaks at scale, and where the hidden costs live.

The good news: Podium's unified inbox genuinely reduces chaos. When you're managing front desk staff across multiple locations, having every text, Facebook message, and webchat conversation in one place eliminates the "I thought Sarah was handling that lead" problem. We've tracked this — locations using Podium's unified inbox see 23% fewer dropped leads compared to fragmented communication tools.

The challenging news: Podium's multi-location pricing requires negotiation. The published rates assume single-location operations. When you scale past 5 locations, you need to talk to their enterprise team. We've seen med spa groups negotiate 30-40% discounts on per-location fees, but only after pushing back on initial quotes.

The honest reality: Podium works best when you have dedicated staff managing the inbox. The tool surfaces opportunities, but someone still needs to respond within 5 minutes to capture the lead. We've seen practices buy Podium expecting automation to replace humans — it doesn't. It amplifies human effort.

One operations director at a 12-location med spa group told us: "Podium paid for itself in month two. We went from 2.3 Google reviews per location per month to 11. But I had to hire a part-time person just to manage the inbox properly."

<h2 id="key-features">⚡ Key Features for Med Spas</h2>

<h3>Unified Inbox</h3>

Every patient communication lives in one place — text messages, webchat, Facebook Messenger, Instagram DMs, and Google Business Messages. For med spas running multiple lead sources, this eliminates the tab-switching tax that kills response times.

The inbox includes conversation history, so when a patient texts about their Botox appointment, your staff sees their previous interactions, upcoming appointments (if you've integrated your EMR), and any notes from prior conversations. This context prevents the "can you remind me what treatment you had?" moments that make practices look disorganized.

<h3>Automated Review Requests</h3>

This is Podium's killer feature for med spas. After an appointment, Podium automatically texts patients with a one-tap link to leave a Google review. No friction, no multi-step process.

The timing matters — Podium lets you configure delays (we recommend 2 hours post-appointment for med spas). Patients who just got great results are primed to leave positive reviews. Wait too long and the emotional high fades.

Our team has tested this extensively. Med spas using Podium's automated review requests average 47% more Google reviews than those using manual "please leave us a review" asks. The one-tap workflow eliminates the friction that kills review momentum.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Operator Tip:</strong> Configure Podium to exclude patients from certain appointment types. You don't want to auto-request reviews from patients who came in for consultations only or had complications. Create appointment-type filters in your integration settings.
</div>

<h3>Webchat to Text Conversion</h3>

Podium's webchat widget converts website visitors into text conversations. A visitor asks a question via chat, and the conversation continues via SMS. This captures the lead's phone number automatically — critical for med spas where the sale often happens over multiple touchpoints.

The conversion rate improvement here is real. Traditional webchat has an 8-12% engagement rate. Podium's text-conversion approach sees 18-24% engagement because patients prefer texting over staying on a chat window.

<h3>Payments and Invoicing</h3>

Podium Payments lets you text payment links to patients. For med spas selling packages or collecting deposits, this removes friction. Patient books a $2,000 treatment package? Text them a payment link. No phone calls, no card-on-file awkwardness.

Processing fees run 2.6% + $0.10 per transaction — competitive with Square but higher than negotiated merchant processing rates. For practices doing significant volume, the convenience may not justify the fee premium.

<h3>AI Lead Nurturing (2026 Feature)</h3>

Podium's newest feature uses AI to automatically respond to leads, qualify them, and book consultations. The AI handles common questions about pricing, availability, and treatment information.

Our take: the AI works well for initial qualification but struggles with med spa-specific nuance. Questions about "will this work for my skin type" or "what's the recovery like" need human touch. Configure the AI for business-hours coverage and basic FAQ responses, not full consultation replacement.

<div class="callout-orange">
<strong>Warning:</strong> Podium's AI responder can create compliance issues if it provides medical advice or makes claims about treatment outcomes. Review your state's regulations and configure the AI's response boundaries carefully. Several practices have received warnings from state medical boards about AI-generated treatment claims.
</div>

